Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_594
Response Text: These programs need to focus on performance, music, bringing arts of all genre's to the community.  The prior emphasis on diversity, equity and inclusion, rather than the art, does not insure that all types of performance will be available in Austin.  I understand that underrepresented artists do not always have the ability to prepare grant applications.  But in the past all you had to do was reach out to the Cultural Arts Division staff who hold office hours and are happy to help you prepare your application.  If the interview process remains as part of the grant application, the interviewers must be familiar with the organization's performance repertoire and then interview based on knowledge of the application, the organization and the content of the performance.  Making assumptions about the organization/performer is not an unbiased interview.  I think the three levels of grant applications (Nexus, Thrive and Elevate) are acceptable based on funding.  But there needs to be further breakdown within those levels to insure that the applications are evaluated by knowledgeable reviewers within the genre.

